## 💡 Implementation Details

### **Why This Approach?**

**Smart Protection Strategy**:
- ✅ **Main admin CAN** edit their own details (email, role if needed)
- ✅ **Main admin CAN** reset their own password
- ❌ **Main admin CANNOT** be deleted (prevents losing admin access)
- ❌ **Main admin CANNOT** be deactivated (prevents losing admin access)

**Why hiding buttons instead of disabling?**
- ✅ Cleaner UI - no grayed-out buttons taking up space
- ✅ Clear intent - what you see is what you can do
- ✅ Less confusing - no need for tooltips explaining why buttons are disabled

### **Defense in Depth**

- **Frontend Protection** (UI): Buttons hidden using `*ngIf="!isMainAdmin(user)"`
- **Backend Protection** (API): Delete endpoint returns error for admin@example.com
- **Self-Deactivation Check**: Existing logic prevents any admin from deactivating themselves

